  "prompt": "I tell my crush that I just broke with my girlfriend then I accidentally told her I like her, What should I do now?",
  "response": "It sounds like you're in a complex and delicate situation. Here are a few steps you might consider:\n\n1. **Reflect on Your Feelings**: Make sure you understand your own feelings. It's important to determine if your feelings for your crush are genuine or possibly influenced by your recent breakup.\n\n2. **Acknowledge the Mistake**: If your admission was truly accidental and you're not ready to talk about it further, consider acknowledging it briefly and expressing your regret for any awkwardness you may have caused.\n\n3. **Apologize (if necessary)**: If you feel that your crush might be uncomfortable or taken aback by your admission, a simple and sincere apology might help smooth over the situation.\n\n4. **Give Space**: Allow your crush some time to process what you've said. Respect her feelings and space.\n\n5. **Follow Up**: When the time feels right, you can have a more thoughtful conversation with her. You could explain your situation in more detail and let her know that you value her friendship and understand if she needs time to think about what you've said.\n\n6. **Be Honest and Respectful**: Whatever you decide to say, make sure you're being honest and respectful of her feelings.\n\nRemember, vulnerability can be tough, but honesty and clarity are crucial in any kind of relationship.",
